[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Figuring out object construction**\n\nI’m thinking about the Sun13InstantiatorBase field's protected access and how it compiles. I need to correctly configure the Sun13Instantiator after that. It seems like the newInstance method calls a support method. I wonder if that support method can create an object even without a constructor? I guess we could potentially just return a preconstructed object instead. This way, it feels like there's a solution to the object creation problem!\n\n**Considering method accessibility**\n\nI need to use `Sun13RuntimeSupport.class.getDeclaredMethod` directly, which seems fine. I wonder if I could also utilize a public API; it’s all top-level public anyway. It’s good to note that I can test the package outside the library. Checking build dependencies for ByteBuddy doesn’t seem necessary. I might look into whether there are upstream tests for Sun13, but it seems like I don’t need that either.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0bd8cbeb32a6c4f40169ef7b648658819199a3671e6479290d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp73txvZPIBjN3ut9a3l3ndKDzZj0QcdXngX9kQx_MB0iDru8m1_9Qy8PRVho1wTdO00bFsm3_t7gmjJ4PSXi3413tCLebcEmQpX58kz58zbWuOs732BDi9nh5b6hvRQlbB260pFcJTUt7U6FYvQriBB5Mtn9lELXDQmpiBycyj9iNkCWs1AEisFhTF7hAOpNFNm-x209Qi64CzPCq3h2kPbp0O7-rVQInYtUrltlnghNLfAciTPY6z5fma-BTZdZjqdY9Z0Gl9E1Dve-Y3B3ZYe6pDHYi0BGUlGlAnkUlh8sv43LF3vP5gjTSoOlufiKTwzhUyuHPvw4kiF5QGW3tZco051IyldZUh9WvHyG43pYUY2FZUrKCm_y1u3Y47REa3iby9ljiNW7dtR8J6-IsJO9BS9r4CWdvqAMT--rt14vFOG4Qjp1SoMRHdDK3sxmGJAHwGqufkhCFY_eDwmjILipvNGTf1WwhoXihKDVe-Q9mk9GSpXbu6VPL2X7Szy06VQbIjHPd3AuG2c0FPdB9Dwr2mYVICgohztRKHOUqXd1ecCxU2BHphJqtL6TvCygdkTgtq3KACO5YSLBHBCnKe8EHMNbvQdhGXDWhizVQu9BZnPfvMRCAiBIOrOVCai62SYNamWVFV1ukyRdk4ZrRNBigs2C6t_mlvE-7JMJrLZFYDCASAl2naaqRgykjsACvy1gZ0KxsCRTC9Rs89hRjwoNkyRxTtpX5OTG4wRRREC2YURtcElM14ElQ-wo96rrefQmNcUnUT_gWrOFhKyPRLrhDnz-slFU55CRRk763y2t